### User Preferences - Endpoints tests
@host = http://localhost:8080
@auth = {{host}}/api/auth
@users = {{host}}/api/users

### ===========================================================================
### Utilisateurs pre-crees dans data.sql (mot de passe: 1234)
### ===========================================================================

### 0) Login Admin - Capture du token
# @name loginAdmin
POST {{auth}}/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@example.com",
  "password": "1234"
}

### 1) Recuperer les preferences (devrait etre 204 au premier appel)
GET {{users}}/me/preferences
Accept: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{loginAdmin.response.body.accessToken}}

### 2) Sauvegarder des preferences
PUT {{users}}/me/preferences
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{loginAdmin.response.body.accessToken}}

{
  "preferencesJson": "{\"theme\":{\"theme\":\"dark\",\"themePreset\":\"odin-dark\",\"density\":\"normal\",\"fontSize\":14,\"iconOnlyButtons\":false},\"language\":{\"language\":\"fr\"},\"keybindings\":{\"bindings\":[]},\"dashboard\":{\"widgets\":[],\"customShortcuts\":[],\"widgetSettings\":{}},\"profiles\":{\"profiles\":[],\"activeProfileId\":null}}",
  "lastModified": "2026-03-25T10:00:00Z",
  "version": 1
}

### 3) Recuperer les preferences apres sauvegarde
GET {{users}}/me/preferences
Accept: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{loginAdmin.response.body.accessToken}}

### 4) Tester le conflit (timestamp ancien)
PUT {{users}}/me/preferences
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{loginAdmin.response.body.accessToken}}

{
  "preferencesJson": "{\"theme\":{\"theme\":\"light\"}}",
  "lastModified": "2026-03-24T10:00:00Z",
  "version": 1
}

### 5) Tester sans auth (doit renvoyer 401)
GET {{users}}/me/preferences
Accept: application/json
